Pauly-Wissowa: 29. Halbbd., col. 609-616;
      &#034;Memmius&#034;, #8 (C. Memmius; noted by Cicero as L.F. to distinguish
      him from his relations with the same name; b. ca. 98 B.C.; praetor, 58 B.C.; tribune 66/65
      B.C.; propraetorof Bithynia, 57 B.C.; divorced his wife, 55 B.C.; sought consulship 54 B.C.;
      accused of ambitus and withdrew to Mitylene; returned to Rome 49 B.C.; noted by Cicero as
      already dead, 46 B.C.)

Dict. of Greek and Roman biography and mythology, 1967: v. 2, p.
      1026-1027 (C. Memmius L.F. Gemellus; tribune of the plebs, 66 B.C.; curule aedile, 60 B.C.;
      sought the consulship, 54 B.C.; impeached for ambitus and withdrew to Mytilene)
